# ============================================
# NOTES FOR MULTI-COMPUTER DEVELOPMENT:
# ============================================
# 1. Each developer should copy .env.example to .env.local
# 2. Never commit .env.local or any real credentials
# 3. Use 'git pull --rebase' to avoid merge conflicts
# 4. Run 'npm install' after pulling changes
# 5. Clear .next/ cache if you see weird build issues
# 6. Each computer can have different:
#    - Node versions (use .nvmrc for consistency)
#    - Database connections
#    - IDE settings
#    - OS-specific files



